        ]
      },
      "date": "2013-04-13 13:39:42.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Verified\n\nTests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 6.4/x86_64: (https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/ce183710-a43a-11e2-80ee-52540035b04c).  Ran 14 tests.  No failures.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "ab9ccefe81a002c449ec43078242cf7809751790",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-13 18:10:59.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nJust to verify - the layout is still returned in the LVB unless it is very large, correct?  What us the maximum size of inline layout that will be returned?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "9384e47b035c5721ee0c535d58ed77cfb16f63c9",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-04-13 18:20:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n\"Just to verify - the layout is still returned in the LVB unless it is very large, correct? What us the maximum size of inline layout that will be returned?\"\n\nI think this is very reasonable and I would like to do that, but Alex thought we shouldn't access storage in dlm callback at all. So right now in this patch, I'm using one extra getxattr to fetch layout anyways.\n\nHowever, I don't delete the code in dlm layer to support returning layout in completion AST buffer. Therefore after LU infrastructure problem is fixed, we can activate the code to return small layout within completion AST easily.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "338e1c68c5ce0ce5db7318d80d40b60247e3e28b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-13 19:29:45.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nPlease clarify further. Under what circumstances will separate RPC be needed to fetch the layout?\n\nWill the layout (at least all small layouts < 4096 bytes for example) be returned with the initial DLM request?\n\nWill an extra RPC only be needed if there is contention on the layout lock?\n\nThis is pretty important to clarify, since we don't want e.g. two RPCs for every lock enqueue even with small layouts.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "a2ef6db65214d4b13aa2c319788c75915904ccb9",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-04-13 19:43:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n\"Please clarify further. Under what circumstances will separate RPC be needed to fetch the layout?\"\n\nIf enqueuing IT_LAYOUT has a contention, separate RPC will be needed to fetch layout. Usually the layout lock and layout is piggybacked GETATTR or OPEN request. IT_LAYOUT will happen if layout lock is lost on the client.\n\n\"Will the layout (at least all small layouts < 4096 bytes for example) be returned with the initial DLM request?\"\n\nIf there is no contention, layout will be returned within DLM reply. We assume that DLM request has allocated enough space for layout.\n\n\"Will an extra RPC only be needed if there is contention on the layout lock?\"\n\nYes.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "c388c40a39206d9146f1402058767baac601c7dd",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-14 04:47:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\n",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
