      "date": "2013-04-16 12:50:13.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nwhy can't we just put layout in the reply as we did before? and do not \"play\" with LVB at all?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "4418cac5df507cb6acb886e9a722c0a0209fc730",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-04-16 15:17:05.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nLVB of DLM reply has enough space for that. For normal DLM lock requesting that is the only buffer we can use.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "242645b5a974a6c84869bd704a0dab76a173d9c5",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-16 15:22:38.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> LVB of DLM reply has enough space for that. For normal DLM lock requesting that is the only buffer we can use.\n\nthis makes the code much less readable. in case of normal DLM lock request (IT_LAYTOUT, i guess) we decided to proceed with extra RPC ?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "dd09b2ed2ad1bf05c3c32badd977459bbd94f0c1",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-04-16 15:30:01.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nIn that case, patch set 1 is what you want. However, I like patch set 2 because I don't think it makes more sense to have an extra RPC to transfer layout now that we have enough space in the enqueue RPC.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "86a385e672da7ea09e204809fdac856eba80c3fd",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-16 15:34:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> In that case, patch set 1 is what you want. However, I like patch set 2 because I don't think it makes more sense to have an extra RPC to transfer layout now that we have enough space in the enqueue RPC.\n\n#1 is not any better in this regard. I think this is not very nice to use LVB as it makes the code pretty hard to understand and maintain. one very rare RPC can't justify this, imo. we're doing number of extra RPCs (readdir, mkdir, etc) and we're fine with that.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
